  "chapters": [
    {
      "number": 1,
      "verses": [
        {
          "text": "We believe in God, the Eternal Father, and in His Son, Jesus Christ, and in the Holy Ghost.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Believe.",
              "start": 3,
              "end": 10
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Godhead; God the Father, Elohim.",
              "start": 14,
              "end": 17
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Jesus Christ, Divine Sonship.",
              "start": 50,
              "end": 53
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Holy Ghost.",
              "start": 80,
              "end": 90
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe that men will be punished for their own sins, and not for Adam's transgression.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Punish.",
              "start": 28,
              "end": 36
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Ex. 32:33; Deut. 24:16; Ezek. 18:20 (1–20). TG Accountability; Agency.",
              "start": 47,
              "end": 50
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Fall of Man.",
              "start": 69,
              "end": 75
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe that through the Atonement of Christ, all mankind may be saved, by obedience to the laws and ordinances of the Gospel.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Jesus Christ, Atonement through.",
              "start": 28,
              "end": 37
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Jude 1:3.",
              "start": 53,
              "end": 60
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Ps. 49:15; Mosiah 27:24 (24–26); D&C 93:38; Moses 5:9. TG Salvation.",
              "start": 68,
              "end": 73
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe that the first principles and ordinances of the Gospel are: first, Faith in the Lord Jesus Christ; second, Repentance; third, Baptism by immersion for the remission of sins; fourth, Laying on of hands for the gift of the Holy Ghost.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Ordinance.",
              "start": 41,
              "end": 51
            },
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 138:33. TG Baptism, Qualifications for; Faith.",
              "start": 78,
              "end": 83
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Repent.",
              "start": 118,
              "end": 128
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Baptism.",
              "start": 137,
              "end": 144
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Baptism, Immersion.",
              "start": 148,
              "end": 157
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Remission of Sins.",
              "start": 166,
              "end": 175
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Hands, Laying on of.",
              "start": 206,
              "end": 211
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Holy Ghost, Gift of.",
              "start": 220,
              "end": 224
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [
            {
              "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
              "data-pointer-type": "media",
              "data-scroll-id": "p4",
              "title": "Associated Content"
            }
          ],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe that a man must be called of God, by prophecy, and by the laying on of hands by those who are in authority, to preach the Gospel and administer in the ordinances thereof.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "Num. 27:16 (15–20). TG Called of God; Priesthood, Qualifying for.",
              "start": 30,
              "end": 36
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Prophecy.",
              "start": 48,
              "end": 56
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Hands, Laying on of.",
              "start": 82,
              "end": 87
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Authority; Priesthood, Authority.",
              "start": 108,
              "end": 117
            },
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 11:15 (15–21). TG Preaching.",
              "start": 122,
              "end": 128
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Alma 13:16 (8–16).",
              "start": 162,
              "end": 172
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [
            {
              "class": "iconPointer-OKie_ icon-eLakR icon-ieVZ1",
              "data-pointer-type": "media",
              "data-scroll-id": "p5",
              "title": "Associated Content"
            }
          ],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe in the same organization that existed in the Primitive Church, namely, apostles, prophets, pastors, teachers, evangelists, and so forth.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Church Organization.",
              "start": 23,
              "end": 35
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Prophets, Mission of.",
              "start": 92,
              "end": 100
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Bishop.",
              "start": 102,
              "end": 109
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Teacher; Teacher, Aaronic Priesthood.",
              "start": 111,
              "end": 119
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Patriarch.",
              "start": 121,
              "end": 132
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe in the gift of tongues, prophecy, revelation, visions, healing, interpretation of tongues, and so forth.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Holy Ghost, Gifts of.",
              "start": 18,
              "end": 22
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Language.",
              "start": 26,
              "end": 33
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Prophecy.",
              "start": 35,
              "end": 43
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Revelation.",
              "start": 45,
              "end": 55
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Vision.",
              "start": 57,
              "end": 64
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Heal.",
              "start": 66,
              "end": 73
            },
            {
              "footnote": "1 Cor. 12:10; Morm. 9:7.",
              "start": 75,
              "end": 89
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe the Bible to be the word of God as far as it is translated correctly; we also believe the Book of Mormon to be the word of God.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Bible; Revelation; Scriptures, Preservation of; Scriptures, Value of; Scriptures, Writing of.",
              "start": 15,
              "end": 20
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Isa. 8:20 (16–22).",
              "start": 31,
              "end": 35
            },
            {
              "footnote": "1 Ne. 13:26 (20–40); 14:21 (20–26).",
              "start": 70,
              "end": 79
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Book of Mormon.",
              "start": 101,
              "end": 115
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe all that God has revealed, all that He does now reveal, and we believe that He will yet reveal many great and important things pertaining to the Kingdom of God.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "TG Revelation.",
              "start": 28,
              "end": 36
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Dan. 2:28 (22–29, 49); Amos 3:7; D&C 121:26 (26–33). TG Scriptures to Come Forth.",
              "start": 99,
              "end": 105
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe in the literal gathering of Israel and in the restoration of the Ten Tribes; that Zion (the New Jerusalem) will be built upon the American continent; that Christ will reign personally upon the earth; and, that the earth will be renewed and receive its paradisiacal glory.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "Isa. 49:22 (20–22); 60:4; 1 Ne. 19:16 (16–17). TG Israel, Gathering of.",
              "start": 26,
              "end": 35
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Israel, Ten Lost Tribes of.",
              "start": 76,
              "end": 86
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Ether 13:6 (2–11); D&C 42:9; 45:66 (66–67); 84:2 (2–5); Moses 7:62. TG Jerusalem, New; Zion.",
              "start": 93,
              "end": 97
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Micah 4:7. TG Jesus Christ, Millennial Reign.",
              "start": 178,
              "end": 183
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Earth, Cleansing of; Earth, Renewal of; Eden.",
              "start": 239,
              "end": 246
            },
            {
              "footnote": "IE a condition like the Garden of Eden; see Isa. 11:1–9; 35; 51:1–3; 65:17–25; Ezek. 36:35 (1–38); 2 Ne. 8:1–3. TG Paradise.",
              "start": 263,
              "end": 275
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Glory.",
              "start": 276,
              "end": 281
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We claim the privilege of worshiping Almighty God according to the dictates of our own conscience, and allow all men the same privilege, let them worship how, where, or what they may.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "Alma 21:22 (21–22); D&C 93:19; 134:4 (1–4).",
              "start": 13,
              "end": 22
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Agency.",
              "start": 67,
              "end": 75
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Conscience.",
              "start": 87,
              "end": 97
            },
            {
              "footnote": "Micah 4:5; D&C 134:7 (4, 7). TG Worship.",
              "start": 146,
              "end": 153
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe in being subject to kings, presidents, rulers, and magistrates, in obeying, honoring, and sustaining the law.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 134:1 (1–11). TG Citizenship; Governments.",
              "start": 20,
              "end": 27
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Kings, Earthly.",
              "start": 31,
              "end": 36
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Obedience.",
              "start": 78,
              "end": 85
            },
            {
              "footnote": "D&C 58:21 (21–23).",
              "start": 116,
              "end": 119
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        },
        {
          "text": "We believe in being honest, true, chaste, benevolent, virtuous, and in doing good to all men; indeed, we may say that we follow the admonition of Paul—We believe all things, we hope all things, we have endured many things, and hope to be able to endure all things. If there is anything virtuous, lovely, or of good report or praiseworthy, we seek after these things.",
          "footnotes": [
            {
              "footnote": "Philip. 4:8.",
              "start": 0,
              "end": 2
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Honesty; Integrity.",
              "start": 20,
              "end": 26
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Chastity.",
              "start": 34,
              "end": 40
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Benevolence.",
              "start": 42,
              "end": 52
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Good Works.",
              "start": 77,
              "end": 81
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Hope.",
              "start": 177,
              "end": 181
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Perseverance; Steadfastness.",
              "start": 246,
              "end": 252
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Modesty; Virtue.",
              "start": 286,
              "end": 294
            },
            {
              "footnote": "TG Beauty.",
              "start": 296,
              "end": 302
            }
          ],
          "associatedContents": [],
          "italics": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
